Please take notice that the BOARD OF EDUCATION OF THE LAKE GEORGE CENTRAL SCHOOL DISTRICT will hold its August 11, 2020, monthly meeting of members of the Boards of Education remotely through electronic means due to the COVID-19 gathering restrictions. Members of the public will be able to attend the meeting via WebEx Event starting at 7 p.m. at the following address: https://lkgeorge.webex.com/lkgeorge/onstage/g.php?MTID=e21e01a88e20868d6989ef2dcb24568d2

Agenda items include a review of the Reentry Plan and information about Remote Learning Plans.

To ask questions during the Board meeting tonight, please email boe@lkgeorge.org

Lake George Elementary School's Kindergarten Roundup for the 2020-2021 school year has been rescheduled. This event will take place from Wednesday, August 19 through Friday, August 21, 2020.

Children who will be five years old on or before December 1, 2020 and live in the Lake George School District are eligible to be enrolled.

Please call Natalie Fullen, Kindergarten Round-Up Coordinator, or the Main Office at 518-668-5714 for further information.

Dear Lake George CSD Families and Staff,
We are awaiting final guidance from Governor Cuomo on school reopening plans in the Fall, which is expected to come on Monday, July 13, 2020. In the meantime, we are convening a K-12 District Level Steering Committee and gathering input from families and staff to begin to formulate a plan that has been mandated to be submitted by July 31, 2020.

We invite you to complete this survey regarding your thoughts and concerns about the possible return to in-person teaching and learning in the Fall ‚¨áÔ∏è

https://www.lkgeorge.org/site/default.aspx?PageType=3&DomainID=8&ModuleInstanceID=1750&ViewID=6446EE88-D30C-497E-9316-3F8874B3E108&RenderLoc=0&FlexDataID=11407&PageID=9

post_text:
We are pleased to announce the annual budget for the 2020-21 school year was approved. The bus proposition was also approved. Thank you to all who came out to vote.

"On behalf of the Lake George Board of Education, students, faculty, staff, and administration, I would like to thank the residents of the Lake George Central School District for approving the 2020-21 spending plan and bus proposition," said Superintendent Lynne Rutnik. "I would also like to extend sincere congratulations to Rosemarie Earl and Jeannine Bieber on being elected to the LGCSD Board of Education. I look forward to their partnership in the years to come."

Budget VOTE Results
Yes Vote = 1,302
No Vote = 561
Invalid = 71

Bus Proposition:
Yes Vote = 1,277
No vote = 576

BoE Members:
Jeannine Bieber 977
Rosemarie Earl. 1,174
Jay Salmon. 480
Tom Seguljic 704

PLEASE READ this important information regarding the 2020-2021 Budget Vote and Board of Education Election.

School Budget Ballots will now be counted on Tuesday, June 16, 2020 beginning at 5 p.m.

Governor Cuomo's Executive Order 202.39 has modified the rules for the District Budget Vote and Board of Education election. Per the order, the District can only accept in-person ballots through 5pm on Tuesday, June 9, 2020. However, ballots delivered by mail will be counted as long as they are received by the district by 5 p.m. on Tuesday, June 16, 2020.

post_text:
Due to the COVID-19 virus, voting for the annual School District Budget and Board of Education election will be done by absentee ballot only. Residents of the Lake George Central School District will begin to receive absentee ballots and the school district budget newsletter in the mail in the coming days.

Absentee ballots need to be completed and received by the district via mail by June 9, 2020 at 5 p.m. (Statewide Uniform Voting Day).

The Official Absentee Ballot envelope that contains your ballot must also include your name, residence, school district, and signature.

Please remember, that in order to qualify to vote, you must be:
1. At least 18-years of age
2. A United States Citizen
3. A legal resident of the district you are voting in for at least 30-days immediately prior to the vote date.
4. Registered to vote in the school district election and/or
registered to vote in your county board of elections

Many thanks to Cooper and Mazie Collins for creating this video reminder!!

https://youtu.be/xSB6FT3m3n8

More great news from the Art Department üé® üñå

The High School Art Department is proud to announce that our Lake George students took home top honors at the 10th Annual YOUTH VISIONS Juried Show in South Glens Falls, sponsored by North Country Arts . They had THREE BEST IN SHOW AWARDS!

Winning students were each given a $75 cash prize and membership to the professional organization for one year.

Congratulations to ~
Alexandra Ehmann - Excellence in Mixed Media
Poe Tutu - Excellence in Jewelry
Tierman Mase - Excellence in Pottery

post_text:
Some wonderful news FROM THE ART DEPARTMENT üé®üñå

1Ô∏è‚É£4Ô∏è‚É£ pieces from of our incredibly talented visual art students made the top 200 in the first round of adjudication at the Annual Hyde High School show‚ÄºÔ∏è

Traditionally, the pieces would next go to live adjudication and from there the final 100 pieces would be selected. Due to social distancing, and because the Hyde is currently closed, the committee has decided they will continue the judging process in a digital format and the presentation of this years show will also be virtual.

Congratulations to ~
Jordan Brophy-Palsson (3 pieces)
Poe Tutu
Kendra Cameron
Brian Dee
Kaylie Morton
Tyler Cornelius
Ava Pushor (2 pieces)
Lila Fazier
Orabel Beachel
Aimee Ehmann

post_text:
Lake George Jr.-Sr. High School was happy to welcome Author
Steve Sheinkin to talk with our students about the writing process and the research required for nonfiction writing.

Mr. Sheinkin's first presentation was to seniors in the American Literature class. He focused on his book, "Undefeated," and the research he did on the historical topic.

His second presentation was for all students in English 9. He talked about his book, "Bomb," nonfiction writing, and the WWII time period.

Mr. Sheinkin's final presentation was on creative writing for the seniors in that class. He talked about the writing process and the specific process he uses.

Many thanks to Mr. Sheinkin for taking the time to share your experiences with our students!

üá´üá∑ French Immersion Day üá´üá∑

Lake George French 12 students and Schroon Lake French students practiced their language skills together during a French Immersion Day at the Hillview Library in Diamond Point.

The students and their teachers were welcomed warmly by their host, Mrs. Louise Higgins, a fluent speaker, and Librarian Mrs. Graves. Mrs. Higgins and Mrs. Graves prepared an authentic French lunch for the students to enjoy.

Madame Higgins shared her own experience and memories as a bed and breakfast owner in Jugon-les-lacs, located in Brittany, France. After, students did presentations ‚Äì all in French ‚Äì about the culture and history of specific areas of France they had researched.

Pictured below are: Mrs. Louise Higgins, Mrs. Royer-Loiselle (French teacher at Schroon Lake), Mara, Jenna, Reya, Lanie, Madame Martineau, Carter, Oliver, Anna, Colby, Paul, Elisabeth.

Lake George Elementary School students celebrated the progress they have made to date on their school-wide Wildly Important Goal (WIG) of improving reading. They held their first Rocking Reading Rally of the year, which also happened to fall on ‚ÄúTime Travel‚Äù Day (which made for some awesome outfits!).

During the Rocking Reading Rally, the class in each grade level with the best average in their reading measure for the month was awarded a trophy. Additionally, the grade level with the highest growth received the coveted Golden Oar.

Congratulations to the following Rocking Readers for the month of February:
Mrs. Hendry‚Äôs Class (kindergarten)
Mrs. Kelly‚Äôs Class (first grade)
Ms. Poetzsch & Ms. Gearing‚Äôs Class (second grade)
Ms. Byrne & Mrs. Gershen‚Äôs Class (third grade)
Mrs. Lindsay‚Äôs Class (fourth grade)
Mrs. Montesano‚Äôs Class (fifth grade)
Mrs. Catarelli & Mrs. Spring‚Äôs Class (sixth grade)

The grade level with the highest growth for February was kindergarten. Congratulations on earning the Golden Oar!

We are so proud of ALL of our LGES Readers!

Keep Reading!

shared_text:
Sweethearts and Heroes
February 13 at 9:37 PM ¬∑

Day #13: #FreeHugsFebruary #Challenge

Wow! Did I meet an amazing individual today. From the moment I arrived at Lake George Jr.-Sr. High School she brought immediate #JOY to my day. Throughout the day we connected and her positive attitude was contagious!

I have no choice but to give today's #FREEHUG shirt to Ashlyn McChesney for making my day even better than it already was! This young woman is truly going to #ChangeTheWorld with her #Attitude. Reminds me of what the great #WilliamJames said:

"The greatest discovery of my generation is that a human being can alter his/her life by altering their attitudes"

We can all learn from this incredible woman!

Thanks #Syracuse!

#Bullying #Antibullying #HOPE #Empathy #ThisWillChangeTheWorld

Lake George CSD
